      <abstract>
        <p>Animalove director Amy Laurent letter on June 6 article scores cockfighting</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The decision to allow or disallow the ''sport'' of cockfighting should not be influenced by campaign finance contributions, as you imply in your June 6 front-page article ''In Rural Enclaves of U.S., Cockfights Are Flourishing.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The decision to allow or disallow the ''sport'' of cockfighting should not be influenced by campaign finance contributions, as you imply in your June 6 front-page article ''In Rural Enclaves of U.S., Cockfights Are Flourishing.''</p>
        <p>This heinous cruelty, inflicted by man upon innocent birds, cannot be tolerated in a civilized society. We do not need yet another legacy of violence to leave our children.</p>
        <p>AMY  LAURENT  Santa Fe, N.M., June 8, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is director of Animalove, an animal rights organization.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
